    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>2 lbs chicken, cut into curry pieces</li>
            <li>2 cups potatoes, peeled and diced</li>
            <li>1 large onion, finely chopped</li>
            <li>3 cloves garlic, minced</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon ginger, grated</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons curry powder</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon turmeric powder</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon cumin</li>
            <li>1 can (14 oz) coconut milk</li>
            <li>2 cups chicken broth</li>
            <li>Salt and pepper to taste</li>
            <li>3 tablespoons vegetable oil</li>
            <li>Fresh cilantro for garnish</li>
            <li>Cooked rice for serving</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>In a large pot, heat vegetable oil over medium heat. Add chopped onions, garlic, and ginger. Saut√© until the onions are translucent.</li>
            <li>Add curry powder, turmeric, and cumin. Stir well to combine.</li>
            <li>Add chicken pieces and cook until browned on all sides.</li>
            <li>Add diced potatoes, coconut milk, and chicken broth. Season with salt and pepper. Bring to a simmer and cook until the chicken and potatoes are tender.</li>
            <li>Adjust seasoning to taste. If the curry is too thick, you can add more chicken broth.</li>
            <li>Serve hot over cooked rice, garnished with fresh cilantro.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your flavorful Kuma Curry!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>
